data.name: Guacamole with Bacon
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy avocado dip enhanced with crispy bacon for a savory twist.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook the bacon in a skillet over medium heat until crispy. Remove and let it drain on paper towels.
Cut the avocados in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a bowl.
Mash the avocado with a fork until your desired consistency is reached (smooth or chunky).
Add the diced red onion, tomato, and cilantro to the bowl.
Squeeze the lime juice over the mixture to add flavor and prevent browning.
Crumble the cooked bacon and fold it into the guacamole.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips or as a topping for your favorite dishes.
